CFS File Manager Table Definitions

The following are configuration parameters used to configure the CFS File Manager Application either for each platform or for a mission as a whole.

Global FM_APP_NAME

File Manager Application Name

Global FM_APP_PIPE_DEPTH

File Manager Command Pipe Depth

Global FM_APP_PIPE_NAME

File Manager Command Pipe Name

Global FM_CHILD_FILE_BLOCK_SIZE

Child Task File I/O Control Settings

Global FM_CHILD_QUEUE_DEPTH

Child Task Command Queue Entry Count

Global FM_CHILD_SEM_NAME

Child Task Semaphore Name - cFE object name

Global FM_CHILD_STAT_SLEEP_MS

Child file stat sleep

Global FM_CHILD_TASK_NAME

Child Task Name - cFE object name

Global FM_CHILD_TASK_PRIORITY

Child Task Execution Priority

Global FM_CHILD_TASK_STACK_SIZE

Child Task Stack Size

Global FM_DIR_LIST_FILE_DEFNAME

Default Directory List Output Filename

Global FM_DIR_LIST_FILE_ENTRIES

Maximum Directory List Output File Entries

Global FM_DIR_LIST_FILE_SUBTYPE

Directory List Output File Header Sub-Type

Global FM_DIR_LIST_PKT_ENTRIES

Directory List Telemetry Packet Entry Count

Global FM_TABLE_CFE_NAME

Free Space Table Name - cFE object name

Global FM_TABLE_DEF_DESC

Free Space Table Description

Global FM_TABLE_DEF_NAME

Free Space Table Name - filename with path

Global FM_TABLE_ENTRY_COUNT

Number of Free Space Table Entries

Global FM_TABLE_FILENAME

Free Space Table Name - filename without path

Global FM_TABLE_VALIDATION_ERR

Table Data Validation Error Code
